http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0116334/|For Ever Mozart (1996)|The first point that calls the attention in For Ever Mozart is the absence of a plot summary in IMDb. The explanation is simple since there is no story, screenplay, plot or whatever might recall the minimum structure of a movie. Jean-Luc Godard is one of the most overrated and pretentious directors of the cinema industry and this pointless crap is among his most hermetic films. I believe that neither himself has understood what is this story about; but there are intellectuals that elucubrate to justify or explain this messy movie, and it is funny to read their reviews. <br /><br />My vote is one.<br /><br />Title (Brazil): Para Sempre Mozart (Forever Mozart)|0.655039473337|0.157597003252|0.344960526663
